    "causal_summary": "Before any rename, the in-scope surface must be frozen into a fully-classified rename map partitioned by dependency closure, pinned to the CURRENT migration tip (not the authoring SHA). Every candidate is classified exactly once (rename/exempt/frozen/generated/tool-mandated) with no 'unknown' bucket; rename entries carry a pending vs already-applied disposition because concurrent v4 work has landed part of the surface (the sk-git kebab pilot). The map is hashed with BASE so execution is reproducible, and the generated .codex/prompts surface is in scope, classified generated.",
